***********************************************
*********** TESTING STUFF WITH BATS ***********
***********************************************

****** BATS CORE CONFIGURATION ******

Sample for launching BATS test from this folder:

$ bats sample.sh

For installing BATS

$ git clone https://github.com/sstephenson/bats.git
$ cd bats
$ ./install.sh /usr/local

Note that you may need to run install.sh with sudo if you do not have permission to write to the installation prefix.

****** BATS DEPENDENCIES ******

For installing dependencies
$ git submodule init
$ git submodule update

****** RUNNING BATS TESTS ******

To run tests using bats dependencies is mandatory load them using helper method "load_lib" located at test_helper library.

load "./test_helper/load_lib"
 
load_lib bats-assert

@test "addition using bc" {
  result="$(echo 2+2 | bc)"
  assert_equal "$result" 4
}

